  "description": "<p>Head for the lifts or ski the backbowl with a jacket that has every feature you need. The Bromont Recycled Down Jacket packs warmth and wind-resistance worthy of cold environments. Strategically placed warm-when-wet synthetic insulation in exposed areas, and high-loft down throughout the torso seals in body heat. The hood accommodates a helmet, and the powder skirt keeps snow on the hill where it belongs. Plus, the clean design looks sleek as you slide into the lift line.</p><ul><li>2-layer ripstop recycled polyester shell with MEC's VarioShell waterproof-breathable membrane and fully taped seams</li><li>700 fill-power down in the torso with Primaloft Gold synthetic insulation in areas where you risk building up moisture</li><li>Adjustable, helmet compatible hood with stiffened brim for visibility in bad conditions</li><li>Front pockets sit high for backpack and a chest pocket secures small essentials</li><li>Large internal stow pockets for stashing extra gloves or a hat</li><li>Raglan sleeves provide great range of motion and sit well under backpack straps</li><li>Velcro cuffs and drawcord hem blocks out the cold</li><li>Underarm vents let keep you from overheating on warmer days</li><li>Built-in Recco\u00ae Rescue System reflector allows ski patrol and mountain rescue teams to detect and locate it under snow</li></ul>",
